    {
      "role": "user",
      "content": "but \"well-intentioned\" is a pretty loaded way to put it. wasn't the whole point of the intervention supposed to be \"protecting civilians\"? if the end result was just a failed state and more terrorism, isn't it more accurate to say the policy itself was a failure from the start, rather than just an accident?",
